---- Verdict ----
Vulkan end-to-end runs on Mali-G78 after patching ggml-vulkan.cpp:6613 to grow the
descriptor-set pool on demand instead of aborting (the stock assertion fires on
the graph pattern llama.cpp produces for Q4_0 1B-class models on this GPU).

Numerically, Mali-G78 is SLOWER than 4-thread CPU for LLM inference on this chip,
by a large margin on prompt processing and a moderate margin on token generation.
This is consistent with Mali having no matrix cores, only 32KiB shared memory,
and warp size 16 — hardware that is not tuned for Q4_0 mat-vec, which is memory
bandwidth-bound and benefits little from the GPU's parallelism vs the CPU's NEON.

Real Pixel 6 LLM acceleration would require Edge TPU / NNAPI (Tensor G1 has an
Edge TPU), which neither llama.cpp nor the Q4_0 quant format target.  Moonshine,
Whisper, or TFLite .tflite models through the NNAPI delegate are the path there.

